<Sect1 Id="PrintingMessagesTA">
<Title>To Print Mail Messages within Mailer</Title>
<IndexTerm><Primary>printing messages</Primary></IndexTerm>
<IndexTerm><Primary>messages, printing</Primary></IndexTerm>
<Para>You can print a message using the default options or
you can set different print options.
</Para>
<Procedure>
<Title>To Print a Message with the Default Options</Title>
<IndexTerm>
<Primary>printing messages, using default options</Primary>
</IndexTerm>
<IndexTerm>
<Primary>messages, printing using default options</Primary>
</IndexTerm>
<Step>
<OrderedList Role="tight">
<ListItem Id="HMLR.TSKS.item.104">
<Para>Select the message to be printed in the Message Header list.
</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem Id="HMLR.TSKS.item.105">
<Para>Click the Print button.
</Para>
</ListItem>
</OrderedList>
</Step>
</Procedure>
<Procedure>
<Title>To Print a Message with Specific Options</Title>
<IndexTerm>
<Primary>printing messages, using specific options</Primary></IndexTerm>
<IndexTerm><Primary>messages, printing using specific options</Primary></IndexTerm>
<Step>
<OrderedList Role="tight">
<ListItem Id="HMLR.TSKS.item.106">
<Para>Select the message to be printed in the Message Header list.</Para>
<para>Shift+Click enables you to select several messages in a row by moving
the highlight up or down the message header list. Control+Click enables you
to select discontiguous messages one at a time from the list.
</para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem Id="HMLR.TSKS.item.107">
<Para>
Choose Print... from the Message menu or press Control+P.
</Para>
<para>
The Print dialog box appears.
</para>
<graphic entityref="MailerPrintDialogBox" Id="HMLR.TASKS.fig.1"></Graphic>
<itemizedlist remap="Bullet2"><listitem><para>To select a different printer,
type the new printer name in the Printer Name field.</para>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<para>
To output multiple copies, type
the number of copies in the Copies field.
</para>
</listitem>
<listitem><para>To print to a file, click the Print to File checkbox
and type the path and filename for the file.
</para>
</listitem>
<listitem><para>To submit multiple messages as individual print
jobs, click the Print Separately checkbox.
</para>
</listitem>
<listitem><para>To have long lines wrap to fit the page size,
click the Use Word Wrap checkbox.
</para>
</listitem>
</itemizedlist>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<para>
To set additional options, click the More... button.
The Mailer - Mail Options dialog box appears so
you can set additional options for headers and footers, margins,
printed message headers, and the multiple message separator.
See <XRef Linkend="MailPrintOptions">.
</para>
<para>
When finished setting the Print Options, click OK to establish your
choices as the new defaults and return to the Print dialog box. When you
print with default options, your new settings will be used.
Apply sets the new defaults, but remains in this dialog box.
Reset restores the options to their previous settings. Cancel cancels
any changes since the last Apply and returns you to the Print dialog box.
</para>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<para>
To set printer-specific options, click the Setup... button on the Print dialog box.
The Print Setup window appears. From this window, you can
examine printer information and define both Printer and Job options.
See
<olink type="Jump" LocalInfo="PrnSetup PrintSetupRef">Print Setup
Window</OLink> for more information.
</para>
<para>
When finished with the Print Setup window, click OK to set your changes
and return to the Print dialog box.
</para>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<para>To send the selected message(s) to the printer from the
Print dialog box, click Print.</para>
</listitem>
</orderedlist>
</Step>
</Procedure>
