<Sect1 Id="MailTemplatesTA">
<Title>To Create Templates for Mail Messages</Title>
<IndexTerm>
<Primary>templates, creating for mail messages</Primary>
</IndexTerm>
<IndexTerm>
<Primary>messages, creating mail templates for</Primary>
</IndexTerm>
<Para>You may want to create a template (file) that contains text
you frequently use when composing messages, such as a status
report format or signature and closing message.</Para>
<OrderedList Role="tight">
<ListItem Id="HMLR.TSKS.item.227">
<Para>Create your template using a text editor and save it in your file
system.
</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem Id="HMLR.TSKS.item.228">
<Para>Add the template to the Format menu using the Template options.
</Para>
<Para>For more information, see the <XRef Linkend="MailTemplateOptions">.
</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem Id="HMLR.TSKS.item.229">
<Para>Choose New Message from the Compose menu.
</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem Id="HMLR.TSKS.item.230">
<Para>Choose Templates from the Format menu and select the
correct template from the list.
</Para>
<Para>Your template is added to your mail message.
</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem Id="HMLR.TSKS.item.231">
<Para>Add text to the mail message.
</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem Id="HMLR.TSKS.item.232">
<Para>Send the message as usual.
</Para>
</ListItem>
</OrderedList>
<Procedure>
<Title>See Also</Title>
<Step>
